  "sites_vitrines.services.responsive.text": "A site perfectly adapted to all screens, designed first for smooth mobile navigation.",

  "sites_vitrines.compare.title": "Why a custom showcase site rather than another approach?",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.intro": "A showcase site doesn't have the same constraints as an online store: the stakes are often <strong>clarity</strong>, <strong>speed</strong> and <strong>credibility</strong>, without the weight of a large CMS. In the table, columns run from <strong>custom build</strong> through <strong>advanced no-code tools</strong> (Webflow, Framer) to the most common approaches at the end: <strong>WordPress</strong> then <strong>Wix / Squarespace</strong>. Adapt to your sector and update rhythm.",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.caption": "Indicative summary for independents, artisans and local businesses; your project may combine several approaches over time.",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.region": "Showcase website approach comparison table",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.criterion": "Criterion",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.custom": "Custom static site",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.webflow": "Webflow / Framer",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.webflow_sub": "advanced no-code",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.wordpress": "WordPress",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.wordpress_sub": "+ theme / page builder",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.wix": "Wix / Squarespace",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.th.wix_sub": "site builders",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.philosophy": "Philosophy",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.philosophy.custom": "Targeted HTML, CSS and JavaScript: only what's needed for your message",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.philosophy.webflow": "Advanced design in a visual editor, export or hosting tied to the tool",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.philosophy.wordpress": "Dynamic site with database and extension ecosystem",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.philosophy.wix": "Hosted all-in-one, templates and modules built into the platform",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.performance": "Performance",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.performance.custom": "Very fast: few requests, no PHP engine on load",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.performance.webflow": "Good if well optimized, but often heavy JS/CSS load",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.performance.wordpress": "Variable: depends on theme, plugin count and cache",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.performance.wix": "Often adequate, sometimes limited by template and platform scripts",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.security": "Security &amp; maintenance",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.security.custom": "Minimal attack surface: no admin login exposed by default",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.security.webflow": "Depends on platform; monitoring of projects and subscriptions",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.security.wordpress": "WP, theme and plugin updates to track or risk vulnerabilities",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.security.wix": "Managed by vendor, less control over the stack",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.cost": "Cost over time",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.cost.custom": "Light hosting (often very affordable) without a \"engine\" subscription",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.cost.webflow": "Often high editor subscriptions for site + collaboration",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.cost.wordpress": "Hosting + paid extensions + time spent on updates",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.cost.wix": "Monthly or annual plans, options often billed in chains",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.seo": "SEO &amp; structure",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.seo.custom": "Tags and content controlled end to end, without unnecessary layers",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.seo.webflow": "Fine control possible, but discipline needed in the editor",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.seo.wordpress": "Very good if well configured; risk of slowness or duplication",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.seo.wix": "Adequate for essentials, sometimes less flexible on fine technical points",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.design": "Design freedom",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.design.custom": "Unique design, not locked into a generic theme",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.design.webflow": "Very creative in the tool, sometimes at the cost of a learning curve",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.design.wordpress": "Large theme choice; deep customization = technical debt",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.design.wix": "Limited to blocks and styles offered by the builder",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.ownership": "Ownership &amp; portability",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.ownership.custom": "You own the files: change host without \"unlocking\" a CMS",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.ownership.webflow": "Often tied to the tool ecosystem or partial export",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.ownership.wordpress": "Export possible but migration often delicate",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.ownership.wix": "Strong lock-in: leaving the platform often means rebuilding everything",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.updates": "Content updates",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.updates.custom": "No built-in dashboard: ideal if the showcase changes little or via occasional missions",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.updates.webflow": "Editing in the tool; collaboration possible depending on plan",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.updates.wordpress": "Rich editing interface; each extension adds complexity",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.updates.wix": "Simple visual editing for common text and images",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.usecase": "Typical use case",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.usecase.custom": "Brand image, clear offer, lightweight pages, contact / booking",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.usecase.webflow": "Design teams that iterate often on the site in the editor",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.usecase.wordpress": "Active blog, many pages, need for specific plugins",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.row.usecase.wix": "Very fast launch with few technical requirements",

  "sites_vitrines.compare.outro.title": "A showcase that belongs to you — without technical debt or editor lock-in",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.outro.p1": "With a custom static site, the idea isn't to trap you in obscure code, but to <strong>remove what doesn't serve your business</strong>: no WordPress dashboard to monitor, no plugins that break after an update, no builder subscription to unlock a \"premium\" option. You keep control of your online presence: the files are yours, hosting stays simple, and performance follows naturally — which strengthens credibility with visitors and Google alike.",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.outro.p2": "For new text, visuals or sections, two approaches work well: <strong>on-demand occasional updates</strong> with someone who already knows your site, or an arrangement where you centralize content (documents, photos) and I integrate it cleanly — without forcing you to become a CMS system administrator for a showcase that often evolves in bursts.",
  "sites_vitrines.compare.outro.p3": "In short: you are not <strong>dependent on a platform</strong> that raises prices or changes rules overnight, nor on a chain of plugins to display a page correctly. The developer intervenes where they add the most value — design, integration, performance, accessibility — and lets your message breathe, without superfluous software between you and your clients.",

